      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "0f186c764e3edc64",
      "text": "During system startup, spikes may occur in the levels of ammonia (up to 6.0 ppm) and nitrite (up to 15 ppm), with nitrate levels peaking later in the startup phase. Since the nitrification process acidifies the water, non-[[sodium]] bases such as [[potassium hydroxide]] or [[calcium hydroxide]] can be added for neutralizing the water's [[pH]] if insufficient quantities are naturally present in the water to provide a buffer against acidification."
    },
